The opportunity
ING is looking for a Data Quality Analyst to drive the building of data quality (DQ) rules, DQ dashboards and DQ issue remediation within Risk and Finance. The role has a primary focus on DQ for Compliance, Non-Financial Risk and Credit Risk modelling.
Are you looking for the opportunity to work with data in the area of risk and finance and to work with a broad international network of people to address key DQ issues, then this job is something to apply for!
The team
You will be part of the Risk Data Quality team consisting of 4 colleagues working from Amsterdam and 4 colleagues that are based in Manilla. The team follows an agile way of working in which it provide services to the Risk and Finance stakeholders within the ING organization. Openness in communication, passion for data and “can do” mentality are important characteristics of the team.
Roles and responsibilities
As a Data Quality Analyst you will drive the following activities:
design and implementation of data quality checks on completeness, accuracy, validity and consistency of data;
development and reporting of data quality dashboards, this also includes the bankwide integrated DQ dashboard that gives insight into the various risk and finance domains & reports of the bank such as the customer domain, granular data reporting and Credit/Market/Non-Financial Risk ;
data quality issue remediation process with the different stakeholders in the organization both centrally and locally: analysis of the root cause of the data quality issues, subsequently prioritize and solve the issues from the different internal and regulatory reports;
ambassador of data quality in the risk, finance and data management organization;
In this role, you will work closely with colleagues from head office (e.g. Non-Financial Risk, Global Data Management, Change organization) and with the data stewards and data quality officers in the local business units.
How to succeed
We hire smart people like you for your potential. Our biggest expectation is that you’ll stay curious. Keep learning. Take on responsibility. In return, we’ll back you to develop into an even more awesome version of yourself.
