About the job
For the Supply Chain department in our Specialized Nutrition factory (Supply point) in Zoetermeer, we are looking for a Master Data Officer. As our new Master Data Officer, you will be responsible for maintaining our master data in various business systems. You will play a key role in master data reporting and in ensuring that the standards and procedures will be followed. Do you have what it takes and are you ready for your next challenge?
Master Data Officer(location: Zoetermeer – Fulltime)

The Master Data Officer is responsible for the accurate, consistent and timely entry of vendor, customer, material and bill of material data into various business systems. To protect the quality of the data, you will play a key role in ensuring that the procedures for data maintenance requests and approvals will be followed.

From this pivotal position you will be responsible for Supply Point Zoetermeer and our new central warehouse in Haps:
Process requests for entry, control and update of vendor, customer, material and bills of material related master data;
Generate data extracts and (KPI) reports;
Perform quality, consistency, completeness and duplication checks;
Monitor, proactively follow and maintain the master data processes and documentation in line with business and system requirements/procedures;
Initiate and drive regular data clean up processes with the relevant data owners;
Provide master data support to and work with the cross functional user community on continuous data quality, process and system improvement projects.
This role will give you the opportunity to grow into the role of Digital Coordinator Supply Chain Systems.
About you
As our new Master Data Officer, you are an energetic self-starter and are naturally organized and structured. You are digital savvy and keen to keep pace with the current developments for digital solutions. You are highly experienced in maintaining and analyzing master data. Moreover, you have demonstrated potential to collaborate with experts across diverse disciplines.

Furthermore you have:
A Bachelor degree, with degree in Information Systems or Supply Chain preferred;
At least 2 years of proven experience in a similar role with the entry and analysis of master data;
Experience with SAP MM/SD preferred or another ERP package (e.g. Oracle, PeopleSoft);
You have experience with setting up and working with workflow tools and process automation tools (RPA);
You have advanced knowledge of MS-Excel, MS-Access, SQL and Power BI;
You have strong analytical and reporting skills;
You are accurate and exact to do things ‘first time right’;
You are able to prioritize and work independently;
Excellent communication skills in English, preferably also in Dutch.
