You provide feedback on project and mobilisation performance to seismic delivery team and make suggestions for improvement;
You assist with training and knowledge dissemination.
Your track record
You have a high standard of general education, you have previous experience with both 2D and 3D seismic operations and you are familiar with geographical data and geodesic systems;
You have good knowledge of Fugro Starfix Software (including Seismic Solution and Seismic Navigation QC widgets), UKOOA and OGP formats and are keen to learn in detail when required;
You are able to assist in remote trouble shooting, and have experience in logsheet and report file handling;
You are familiar with quality control logic and corresponding mathematics;
You have excellent communication skills in English (verbal and written).
